  <body>
    <segment id="1">
Tax free!</segment>
    <segment id="11" parent="16" relname="evidence"> 

Tobacco, alcohol, trade, income, property, entertainment, vehicle, capital gains, and now as of January 1, 2002, also a construction withholding tax.</segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="12" relname="interpretation">  

Germany is not modest,</segment>
    <segment id="12" parent="15" relname="span"> 

when it comes to taking money from its citizens and investors.</segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="16" relname="joint">

The tax authorities always find reasons to introduce new taxes.</segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="17" relname="span">  

The capital gains tax had been introduced,</segment>
    <segment id="13" parent="4" relname="purpose"> 

to make money laundering more difficult.</segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="6" relname="concession"> 

The construction withholding tax is now supposedly intended to expose undeclared work.</segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="18" relname="span">  

However, for example, the many &quot;friends&quot; who officially only &quot;help&quot; the black sheep among the builders will actually continue to carry on their mischief by pocketing untaxed money.</segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="14" relname="preparation">  


The construction withholding tax will definitely have an impact:</segment>
    <segment id="14" parent="22" relname="span">  

The tax officials have even more paperwork to move, check and assess.</segment>
    <segment id="8" parent="23" relname="span">

What must not happen under any circumstances is that the processing times for tax matters take even longer than before.</segment>
    <segment id="9" parent="21" relname="span">  

For example, taxpayers who submitted their income tax returns to the Oranienburg tax office in May 2001 are still waiting for their notices.</segment>
    <segment id="10" parent="9" relname="e-elaboration">

Often it&apos;s those who get something back.</segment>
